---
description: "Order Forge Keycloak authentication and realm configuration"
alwaysApply: true
---

Order Forge uses Keycloak (realm: order-forge) as the identity provider.

- Realm name: order-forge
- Client ID: order-forge-client (confidential client)
- We support Authorization Code Flow (recommended)
- All authentication must map Keycloak JWT claims (roles, organization membership) to our EF Core entities
- Use ASP.NET Core Identity + OpenIdConnect (or manual token handling for Direct Grant)
- Tokens must be validated server-side; never expose client secret in frontend
- Docker setup automatically imports order-forge-realm.json on startup